HEADWORD: Metempsychosis
<hw>Me*temp`sy*cho"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/; <?/ beyond, over + <?/ to animate; <?/ in + <?/ soul. See
<er>Psychology</er>.]</ety> <def>The passage of the soul, as an immortal
essence, at the death of the animal body it had inhabited, into another
living body, whether of a brute or a human being; transmigration of
souls.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

